                <head>Holmfirth Chamber of Commerce</head>
                <dateline>
                    <placeName>Holmfirth</placeName>, <date
                        ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-content" calendar="gregorian"
                        when="1865-05-08">May 8, 1865</date>
                </dateline>
                <p rend="center">
                    <hi rend="italic">Resolution of the Holmfirth Chamber of Commerce</hi>.</p>
                <p>At a meeting of the council held on the 8th of May, 1865, the following
                    resolution was unanimously adopted: <list>
                        <item>“That this chamber desires to express its abhorrence of the
                            assassination of the late President of the United States of America, and
                            to offer its sympathy to Mrs. Lincoln and family, and the American
                            people, in their painful bereavement.”</item>
                    </list>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <list>
                            <item>BENJAMIN CRAVEN, <hi rend="italic">President</hi>.</item>
                            <item>SAMUEL S. BOOTH, <hi rend="italic">Secretary</hi>.</item>
                        </list>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
